<item>
            <title>[SPARK-12133] Support dynamic allocation in Spark Streaming</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-12133</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Dynamic allocation is a feature that allows your cluster resources to scale up and down based on the workload. Currently it doesn&apos;t work well with Spark streaming because of several reasons:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(1) Your executors may never be idle since they run something every N seconds&lt;br/&gt;
(2) You should have at least one receiver running always&lt;br/&gt;
(3) The existing heuristics don&apos;t take into account length of batch queue&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The goal of this JIRA is to provide better support for using dynamic allocation in streaming. A design doc will be posted shortly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
